          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Building Capacity for Family-Focused Residential Treatment Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services to award grants in order to support the development and evaluation of family-focused residential treatment programs (substance use disorder treatment programs for pregnant and postpartum women, as well as parents and guardians, which allow their children to remain with them during treatment).</p>]]></text>
